# Using Diskpart
1. Open a command prompt or PowerShell session locally on the VM.
2. Open the disk partition tool
```
C:> diskpart
DISKPART> SAN
SAN Policy : Offline Shared
DISKPART> SAN POLICY=OnlineAll
PS C:\\Windows\\system32> Set-StorageSetting -NewDiskPolicy OnlineAll
PS C:\\Windows\\system32> Get-StorageSetting
NewDiskPolicy ScrubPolicy PSComputerName
\------------- ----------- --------------
OnlineAll IntegrityStreams
C:\\\\>Diskpart
Diskpart> List volume
Diskpart> Select volume X(Where X is the disk volume, you want to bring online)
Diskpart> Online volume
Diskpart> attributes disk clear readonly
Diskpart> clean
Diskpart> exit
```
# Extra Steps

### 1\. **Step 1.** 
Type **regedit** in the Run window.

### 2\. **Step 2.** 
Navigate to the following sub-key and find the **WriteProtect** key on the right panel.
```
HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\StorageDevicePolicies
```

### 3\. **Step 3.** 
If there is no StorageDevicePolicies key, you need to create one. Right-click on **Control**, select **New** and**Key** option in order and then name it as **StorageDevicePolicies.**

![Create New Key](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

### 4\. **Step 4.** 
Right-click**StorageDevicePolicies**, select **New** and**DWORD (32-bit) Value** and then name it as **WriteProtect**.

### 5\. **Step 5.** 
Right-click the newly created **WriteProtect** key and change the Value to **0**. And then click **OK**to exit this window.

### 6\.**Step 6.** 
Check if you can access your storage device and data.
